Mail-IMAPQueue

Mail::IMAPQueue is a module that provides an interface to watch an IMAP mailbox
and process each message in a FIFO fashion, whenever a new one comes in.

It utilizes Mail::IMAPClient as an IMAP client library to access the mailbox.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Mail::IMAPQueue

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Mail-IMAPQueue

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Mail-IMAPQueue

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Mail-IMAPQueue

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Mail-IMAPQueue/


